        dc:description           "FIGURE 15. Cnemaspis chanthaburiensis from the Phnom Samkos Wildlife Sanctuary, Pursat Province, Cardamom Mountains, Cambodia. Upper left and right: adult males (LSUDPC 5056 and 5054, respectively) from Phnom Dalai in the dark and light color pattern phases, respectively. Lower left: subadult male (LSUDPC 2875) from the base of Phnom Samkos. Photographs by LLG. Lower right: ventral view of adult male (LSUDPC 8539) from Khao Kitchakut, Chanthaburi Province, Thailand. Photograph by PLW." ;
